      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JIMARY FREEDOM (1) turned in a plain performance last time when seventh at this track over 411m behind Country Form (24.65) in a Grade 5. Was a winner the start prior. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Has ability and looks hard to stop. MID CITY BOSS (7) has a strong record here with three wins and a minor from eight starts. Hit the frame latest (20.43) when third at Grafton in a Grade 5. Looks one of the chances. OUR MIRACLES (3) was strongly fancied last time but ran below expectations when seventh (21.11), beaten 10 lengths. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. BURNSIDE GARY (6) won as punters' elect last time and is a major player again.",
